<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Envoy Accused of Antigovernment `Insinuation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0102073194 Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA in Greek 31 Jan 94 p 55 </F>
<F P=103> NC0102073194 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] A statement yesterday by U.S. Ambassador Thomas 
Niles in Veryina could be described as insinuation against the 
government. Niles said: "If the Greek Government shows an 
interest in working with us to fight terrorism, certainly, we 
will help." 
  The U.S. ambassador has obviously considered it expedient to 
repeat his reservations over the Greek intention to cooperate. 
In his next sentence, he said: "It will be just enough if the 
Greek Government shows real interest in such cooperation." 
  Regarding his statement following the murder of Mikhail 
Vranopoulos, when he said: "We will catch those guys," Niles 
made the following correction: "I believe murderers such as 
those in `17 November' will be arrested. My remarks came during 
an emotional moment; it was Vranopoulos' funeral. I did not 
mean the United States would do it, but that these people would 
be arrested. Unfortunately, I do not know exactly when they will 
be arrested and I cannot forecast it." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

