<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin: "We Want To Become Members of the EU" </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0202090694 Brussels EUROPE in English 1 Feb 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0202090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels EUROPE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Russia Keen To Join EU -- </F>
Chernomyrdin"; as released by Brussels TEXTLINE database] 
  [Text] Russia will not turn back plans to integrate its 
economy in the world economy, but it needs a "therapy" to 
diminish the effects of the "shock therapy" that it has 
undergone following current economic reforms. This statement 
was made by Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin at a 
press conference in Davos, Switzerland, where he was 
participating in the World Economic Forum. "We want," he added, 
"to become members of the European Union and we want to become 
members of the G-7, turn it into the G-8." The Russian Prime 
Minister, who met in Davos on Sunday [30 January] with OPEC 
Secretary General Dr. Subroto, also said that "we will not 
object if they want to examine the possibility of Russia's 
participation" in the organization of oil exporting countries. 

</TEXT>

