<H3> <TI>   Czech, Estonian Premiers Agree on Free Trade Zone </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU3001180294 Prague CTK in English 1106 GMT 29 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3001180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Davos, Switzerland, Jan 29 (CTK) -- Czech Premier 
Vaclav Klaus and Estonian Premier Mart Laar have agreed that the 
signing of a free trade zone agreement between the two countries 
is a necessity. 
  Speaking after a meeting of the World Economic Forum, the 
two 
premiers told CTK the agreement would "fundamentally" strengthen 
the countries' bilateral economic relations, but that the date 
of signing such an agreement would depend on the progress of 
talks. 
  Klaus added that he had been invited to visit Estonia, and 
that he would probably go some time in May. 

