<F P=101> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   Claes To Sue, Confront Witness in Agusta Affair </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR3101160594 Brussels BELGA in French 1156 GMT 31 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR3101160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed SVD (ADB): "I Have Nothing To Blame Myself </F>
for in the Agusta Affair"; as released by Brussels BELGA 
Database] 
  [Text] Brussels, 31 Jan (BELGA) -- On Monday morning [31 
January], Foreign Minister Claes confirmed to the press that he 
is to sue the newspaper HET LAATSTE NIEUWS for libel. The HET 
LAATSTE NIEUWS Saturday issue incriminated Claes over an alleged 
FrB15 billion bribe deal with the Italian aeronautic company 
Agusta. HET LAATSTE NIEUWS based its allegations on an 
"anonymous witness close to the SP [Flemish Socialist Party]." 
Minister Claes said that he was ready to confront this witness 
at anytime, adding that "it was the only way to prove my 
innocence." 
  During a 90-minute news conference, Minister Claes also 
described in details the role he played as economic affairs 
minister in negotiating, signing, and controlling the purchase 
contract of the 46 Agusta helicopters. "I have nothing to 
reproach myself neither as regards the procedure itself or the 
content. My administration, my government colleagues and I 
myself defended the interests of the Belgian State," said 
Minister Claes, who believes that the Agusta affair remains a 
case of alleged compensation.... 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

