<F P=106> [Peter Norman report: "Lawson Backed for Top Job at OECD"] </F>
  [Excerpt] The British Government is backing Lord Lawson, 
the former chancellor, to be the next secretary-general of the 
Paris-based Organisation for Economic Co-operation and 
Development. 
  The job of running the "club" of 24 industrialised nations 
falls vacant in September when Mr Jean-Claude Paye, the present 
secretary-general, completes his second five-year term of 
office. Mr Paye, a former French diplomat, is again a candidate 
for the job, as is Mr Donald Johnston, a Canadian Liberal 
politician. 
  British Government officials said yesterday that Lord Lawson 
was ideally qualified, pointing out that he was a strong 
supporter of international economic co-operation when 
chancellor. [passage omitted] 

