<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Companies Block EC Plan To Cut Steel Production </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0102130294 Paris AFP in English 1211 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0102130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Davos, Switzerland, Feb 1 -- The EC plan to cut 
overcapacity in its ailing steel industry has been blocked by 
the failure of companies to come up with voluntary reductions, 
Competition Commissioner Karel van Miert said Tuesday [1 
February]. 
  Van Miert said at the World Economic Forum that 
non-state-aided companies had been counted on to volunteer some 
10.5 million tonnes in capacity cuts out of the 30 million 
targeted. 
  But no offers have so far been received and Van Miert 
expressed pessimism whether any would be forthcoming. "We 
cannot meet the objectives laid down in the Braun report" on 
restructuring the industry, he said. 

</TEXT>

