<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EC's Brittan Meets With Spanish Ministers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102194294 Madrid RNE International Spanish 1400 GMT 1 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0102194294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International Spanish 1400 GMT 1 Feb 
94 </F>




<TEXT>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Spanish Foreign Minister Javier Solana is meeting 
Sir Leon Brittan, European commissioner for foreign economic 
affairs and commercial policy, in Madrid. In Community circles, 
Brittan is considered to be a candidate for Jacques Delors' 
replacement as the president of the European Commission. During 
the last few hours [as heard] Leon Brittan met Spanish Prime 
Minister Felipe Gonzalez to explain the aims of his candidacy to 
the presidency of the European Commission. 
  Later the British conservative politician met a group of 
Spanish businessmen to whom he explained the need to make the 
European labor market more flexible. 
  Last night in Brussels the Spanish foreign minister met 
Jacques Delors, current president of the European Commission, 
with whom he discussed, among other items, relations between the 
Community and East Europe and the future enlargement of the 
European Union and Europe's role in the world. 

</TEXT>

