<H3> <TI>   First Bosnian Ambassador Accredited at Foreign Ministry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0102105794 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 1 Feb 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU0102105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Bosnian Ambassador Accredited"] </F>
  [Text] Vienna -- According to Foreign Minister Alois Mock, 
Austria continues to consistently advocate a just and lasting 
peace settlement in the Balkans. Mock stressed this on Monday 
[31 January] in talking to the newly appointed ambassador of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina to Austria, Hadzo Efendic, who paid his first 
visit to the foreign minister. Efendic is the first ambassador 
of his country accredited to Austria. 
  Mock stated that there is certainly no guarantee for a 
speedy 
peace. However, as the development has shown, deviating from 
the aforementioned principles would not bring a solution closer 
in any way. 

</TEXT>

