<F P=100> BENELUX </F>
<F P=101> Netherlands </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dutch Officer Appointed UN Chief of Staff in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0202122594 Rotterdam ALGEMEEN DAGBLAD in Dutch 2 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> BR0202122594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rotterdam ALGEMEEN DAGBLAD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Dutch </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Dutch Officer Appointed UN Chief of </F>
Staff in Bosnia"] 
  [Text] The Hague -- In compliance with UN Secretary General 
Butrus-Ghali's request, the Netherlands will provide the next 
peacekeeping force chief of staff for Bosnia. The post will 
fall vacant on 1 March. 
  Yesterday evening, Defense Minister Ter Beek told the Second 
Chamber that the decision to appoint a Dutch officer was 
justified because the Netherlands has never refused to provide 
troops for UN operations. There are now about 3,000 Dutch 
soldiers in former Yugoslavia. 
  The Dutch officer, whose name was not divulged on the 
grounds 
that he currently resides abroad, will be responsible for 
coordinating the troops together with General Rose. This 
includes, among other things, negotiating with the commanders of 
the warring parties in the area. 

</TEXT>

