<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister on Protecting Polish Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102153294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1249 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102153294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Rostock (DDP/ADN) -- Federal Interior Minister 
Manfred Kanther has acknowledged that action is still needed to 
protect the border between Germany and Poland. During a visit 
to the Federal Border Guard in the Warnemuende District of 
Rostock today, the minister said contacts between the border 
authorities of both countries could be improved. Therefore, he 
is proposing an exchange of liaison officers. He also called on 
border guards to improve their knowledge of each other's 
language. 
  Kanther said Germany will also be providing more equipment 
to 
the Polish police and border security bodies. It is clear that 
the matter of border protection on Germany's eastern border 
demands that all the parties involved accustom thsemselves to 
the new situation, he said. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

