<H3> <TI>   Slovene Foreign Minister Visits Berlin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0102134794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1112 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0102134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Berlin (DDP/ADN) -- Slovene Foreign Minister Lojze 
Peterle, who is also the former prime minister, arrived in the 
German capital today for a two-day visit. He will meet Eberhard 
Diepgen, the governing mayor of Berlin, this afternoon. 
  Peterle has come to the capital at the invitation of the 
Berlin Aspen Institute. He will take part in roundtable talks 
on Europe, Slovenia, and the Balkans on 2 February. Talks with 
business representatives are also planned. 
  Peterle was elected the first prime minister of the first 
democratically elected Slovene Government in May 1990. He held 
the post for two years. The 45-year-old became deputy prime 
minister and foreign minister in 1993. 

