<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Notes Personnel, Equipment Cuts </TI></H3>
<H4>   Bundeswehr To Halt Foreign Missions </H4>
<F P=102> AU0202101894 Munich ARD Television Network in German 2130 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0202101894 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich ARD Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Bundeswehr will not be able to participate in 
any further missions abroad for the time being. This is 
intended to save some 100 million German marks [DM]. In 
addition, the Bundeswehr intends not to fill 1,500 positions 
that will fall vacant in the civilian sphere, to reduce the 
number of noncareer soldiers, and to extend the transfer of 
units to eastern Germany over a longer period of time. These 
are parts of the list of cuts intended to reduce the defense 
budget by DM1.25 billion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

