<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Receives Turkish Cypriot Journalists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0202194694 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1700 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0202194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis said today that the 
Greek Cypriot side insists on a discussion of the substance of 
the Cyprus issue. Kliridhis made the above statement during a 
news conference with 13 Turkish Cypriot journalists at the 
presidential palace. The president expressed the view that the 
UN secretary general does not intend to submit a second package 
of confidence-building measures. He also said that he expects 
that in his letter to the two sides the secretary general will 
say that immediately following the confidence-building measures 
there must be talks on the substance of the Cyprus issue. 
  Replying to a question on whether there will be a new 
package 
of confidence-building measures for Morphou following the 
implementation of the proposed measures, President Kliridhis 
said that after the agreement on the measures, there will be a 
discussion on the substance of the Cyprus issue. President 
Kliridhis said that, according to the Butrus-Ghali map, Morphou 
must be on the Greek side. He added that this is an issue that 
must be discussed in the substance of the Cyprus issue because 
the territorial aspect will not be solved through the 
confidence-building measures. 
  Replying to a Turkish Cypriot correspondent's question, 
President Kliridhis rejected the claim of AKEL [Restorative 
Party of the Working People] General Secretary Dhimitrios 
Khristofias that he is bluffing on the confidence-building 
measures. Kliridhis said that the policy of bluffing does not 
lead anywhere. 
  Asked whether he believes that the Cyprus problem can be 
resolved during his term in office, President Kliridhis said 
that if Ankara and [Turkish Cypriot Leader] Rauf Denktas have 
decided that it is the time for a solution to the Cyprus issue, 
they have the right man to negotiate with. Kliridhis said that 
he does not meet officially with Denktas, as the Turkish Cypriot 
leader insists continuously, because the UN secretary general 
has not proposed such a meeting. In order to have a meeting with 
Denktas, he said, certain topics on the confidence-building 
measures must be arranged first. He added that he does not 
refuse to have social meetings with the Turkish Cypriot leader. 
  Following their meeting with President Kliridhis, the 
Turkish 
Cypriot journalists visited the Um Haram mosque in Larnaca. 
Earlier they visited Omeriye mosque, which is in the old part 
of Nicosia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

