<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   French Foreign Minister Arrives on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0302103294 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0500 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0302103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe arrived in 
Athens last night and was welcomed by Foreign Minister Karolos 
Papoulias. In their brief statements, the two ministers stressed 
the excellent cooperation relations existing between Greece and 
France. Mr. Juppe described as especially excellent the 
activities of the [European Union's] Greek presidency, 
especially on issues concerning the European Union. Mr. 
Papoulias said that they will discuss both bilateral and 
regional issues as well as the crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Mr. Juppe will be received by Prime Minister Andreas 
Papandreou and will also hold talks with Foreign Minister 
Karolos Papoulias and Alternate Foreign Minister Theodhoros 
Pangalos. 

</TEXT>

