<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation Issues Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0302132094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0302132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over regional map] </F>
  [Text] It was announced that there was loss of life and 
property damage as a result of bomb fragments, dropped by 
Turkish Air Force planes during the Zhalah, falling on 
antiaircraft positions along the Iranian border. Turkey 
expressed great regret about the incident and stated that it 
will do everything in its power to compensate for the damages. 
  According to the Foreign Ministry statement, the joint 
Iranian-Turkish delegation which conducted investigations in the 
region on 1 February prepared a joint report following its study 
tour. 
  The Foreign Ministry statement summarizes the report based 
on 
the conclusions of the investigating delegation as follows: It 
was determined that there was loss of life and damage to 
property as a result of bomb fragments ricocheting toward Iran 
after hitting the ground and following the explosion of several 
fragmentation bombs over antiaircraft positions situated along 
the hills bordering Iran. 
  The statement further states that the close friendly 
relations and cooperation between the two countries, which are 
also neighbors, is of great importance to both Iran and Turkey. 
Turkey expresses great regret over this unfortunate incident 
and over the loss of life and damage to property incurred on the 
Iranian citizens. The statement notes: We offer our 
condolences to the families of our Iranian brothers who have 
lost their lives and a swift recovery to the wounded. Turkey 
will do everything in its power to heal the wounds incurred in 
this unfortunate incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

