<H3> <TI>   Economic Delegation To Begin Talks in Tehran </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0302154194 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1435 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0302154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 3 (A.A) -- The 12th term Turkey-Iran 
joint economic commission meetings are scheduled to take place 
in Teheran between Feb 5-10 the Trade and Treasury Under 
Secretariat said in a statement on Thursday [3 February]. 
  The statement also said that State Minister Cemil Erhan will 
head the Turkish delegation at the meetings which will be 
conducted on the technical level in the form of `trade and 
banking', `economic, industrial and technical cooperation,' and 
`communication,' committees. 
  A forth committee will regulate coordination between the 
other three and will be responsible for writing documents that 
will be signed by the ministers. 
  During the meetings, the increase of export to Iran, border 
trade, trade relations on oil with Iran, contractor services, 
exchanges of electrical energy, and precaution to prevent delays 
in payment as well as double taxation will be discussed. 
  A memorandum of understanding is expected to be signed at 
the 
end of the meetings, the statement said. 
  Erhan and accompanying delegation will return to Turkey on 
Feb 10. 

</TEXT>

