<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Czech Premier Praises U.S. Eximbank Funding </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2801212294 Prague CTK in English 2006 GMT 28 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2801212294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Davos, Jan 28 (CTK) -- The fact that the U.S. Exim 
Bank approved guarantees for loans of $317 million to complete 
and modernize Temelin nuclear power has approved again the 
correctness of all the decisions taken by the Czech Government 
regarding Temelin, Premier Vaclav Klaus told CTK today. 
  Klaus arrived on Thursday [28 January] in Switzerland to 
attend the World Economic Forum. 
  Construction of the plant, located in southern Bohemia, 
started in 1986, and from the very beginning it has been 
strongly criticized by environmental organizations, especially 
in neighboring Austria. American banks and manufacturers are 
involved in the project. 
  "It is another reply to those who are falsely accusing us 
both back home and among our southern neighbors," Klaus stated. 
  The bank certainly took this step after careful 
consideration, he said, adding that he had expected the bank to 
make the decision. 

</TEXT>

