<H3> <TI>   EU Welcomes Signing of Political Agreement in Yemen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0202104994 Brussels RAPID Database in English 1 Feb 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0202104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels RAPID Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [EC Document No DOC/PESC/94/5: "Press Statement by the </F>
Presidency on Behalf of the European Union on the Crisis 
Situation in Yemen"] 
  [Text] The European Union having repeatedly shown the 
interest of its member states toward the establishment of an 
everlasting stability in Yemen based on the principles of 
democracy and the respect of human rights, welcomes the signing 
on 18 January, of an agreement by all political parties, 
represented in the committee for national dialogue in the 
Republic of Yemen. This is an important step toward solving the 
serious political crisis in Yemen. 
  The European Union hopes firmly that the agreement will be 
signed soon by Yemen's political leaders and implemented quickly 
thereby fostering a peaceful solution of political problems, and 
strengthening unity and democracy in the best interest of all of 
the Yemeny people. 

</TEXT>

