<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Troop Presence in Bosnia To Be Reviewed in Spring </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0202114594 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 0800 GMT 
2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0202114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Spanish Foreign Minister Javier Solana arrives today 
in Bosnia, where he will visit two of the four detachments 
belonging to the Spanish contingent in the area. Tomorrow in 
Zagreb, he will meet the representative of the UN secretary 
general in former Yugoslavia. A few minutes before leaving 
Javier Solana stated that our country will reconsider the 
presence of Spanish soldiers in Bosnia at the end of the winter. 
  [Begin Solana recording] Maybe when winter ends we will have 
to do a detailed analysis of the situation; we will do it with 
our colleagues, with the countries that also have troops in the 
field, and make a decision, if a peaceful solution to this 
terrible conflict has not been found. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

