<H3> <TI>   German Defense Minister Favors Poland's Accession </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0402120194 Brussels BELGA in French 1856 GMT 3 Feb 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0402120194 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed KVB: "Poland Prepares Itself for Accession </F>
to European Union"; as released by Brussels BELGA Database] 
  [Text] Brussels, 3 Feb (BELGA) -- Poland must become a 
member of NATO as soon as possible, said German Defense Minister 
Volker Ruehe at an international conference on Poland held in 
Brussels. The conference was organized by the Washington-based 
Center for Strategic and International Studies. 
  "In the wake of the recent successful NATO summit, the 
Alliance must follow a magnanimous strategy of integration and 
cooperation. The NATO summit set in motion an irreversible 
process aimed at reorganizing European security," continued the 
defense minister. In his opinion, for historical reasons Poland 
is strongly pushing for accession to all Western institutions. 
  "Germany's neighbors in the East need a political shield 
that 
offers them security and stability. Germany fully supports the 
integration process," said Ruehe. 

</TEXT>

