<H3> <TI>   Dasa To Intensify Space Cooperation With Japan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0202163894 Hamburg DPA in German 1526 GMT 2 Feb 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0202163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Munich -- The German Aerospace AG company (Dasa) is 
intensifying its space commitment in Japan. As Dasa announced 
in Munich today, the Mitsui and Co. Ltd. corporation in Tokyo is 
to safeguard the space interests of the largest German 
enterprises specializing in aerospace and defense technology in 
Japan. The already signed agreement represents an expansion of 
the treaty concluded in 1981 between the Dasa enterprise Erno 
Raumfahrttechnik GmbH (Bremen) and the Japanese trading company 
on noncommercial aerospace projects. 
  Under the leadership of Dasa, a reusable space capsule 
procured by the German Aerospace Agency (Dara) from Russia is 
being equipped with German-Japanese pay loads and components 
under the project name "Express." The capsule is scheduled to 
be launched in the autumn of 1994 from the Kagoshima space 
center on board a Japanese carrier rocket. This project is 
being promoted by the German Research Ministry and the Japanese 
Ministry for International Trade and Industry. 

</TEXT>

