<H3> <TI>   Army Deployed in Calabria To Fight Crime </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0402105294 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1653 GMT 3 
Feb 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0402105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Army Deployed in Calabria, Attacks </F>
on Police Linked"] 
  [Text] Reggio Calabria, 3 Feb (ANSA) -- The first 200 of 
1,350 army personnel deployed in the southern region of Calabria 
arrived here Thursday [3 February] as investigators confirmed 
that the same weapon was used in three separate attacks against 
Carabinieri police in which four officers were killed. 
  One hundred soldiers will be posted to the city's main 
courthouse while the others will replace local police in the 
provinces of Reggio Calabria, Catanzaro and Cosenza for routine 
patrol duties in what has been dubbed Operation Riace, aimed at 
crime-fighting and prevention in the region. 
  Separately, investigators said the same M-12 nine-caliber 
machine-gun was used in attacks December 2, January 18, and 
February 1 against Carabinieri police car patrols in the region. 
No one was injured in the first attack but both members of the 
two-man patrols were killed in the second and third attacks. 

</TEXT>

