<H3> <TI>   Former Intelligence Officials Indicted for Embezzlement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0302132294 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1838 GMT 2 
Feb 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0302132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Formal Indictment of Secret Service </F>
Officials Asked"] 
  [Text] Rome, 2 Feb (ANSA) -- A request was filed here today 
for the formal indictment of seven top secret service officials 
and employees for allegedly embezzling over 60 billion lire, or 
about 35 million dollars, of official funds. The seven were all 
employed by Sisde, the domestic intelligence agency, including 
former Sisde director Riccardo Malpica, his secretary Matilde 
Martucci, and Sisde's former comptroller Maurizio Broccoletti. 
  The missing money was tracked down through bank accounts in 
San Marino whence much of it was said to have been whisked away 
to South America. Preventive detention warrants were issued in 
the case from June last year. 
  The suspects were released, but further enquiries turned up 
new facts and new warrants were issued. Judicial sources said 
Malpica's had changed as a result of recent testimony. 
Initially, he was believed not have touched any of the money 
himself, but he is now said to be one of the team of embezzlers. 
  The new evidence was said to have come in particular from 
Broccoletti, who was taken into custody on June 25 and whose 
testimony claimed that Interior Ministers over 10 years, 
including President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro, were in on secret 
service scams. 
  Preliminary Investigations Magistrate Vincenzo Terranova is 
now being asked to file formal indictments for association to 
commit embezzlement and reuse the money through banking and real 
estate investments. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

