<F P=101> Switzerland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federal Council Member Defends European Union </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0202142094 Bern ATSA/SDAA in French 1520 GMT 1 Feb 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0202142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern ATSA/SDAA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed eh/bl/tp: "Federal Council Member Flavio </F>
Cotti at University of Zurich: There Is no `Realistic Political 
Alternative' to the European Union"; as released by Bern 
ATSA/SDAA database] 
  [Text] Zurich, 1 Feb (ATS) -- Federal Council Member Flavio 
Cotti feels that the process currently under way in Europe is 
similar to that which led to the creation of the Federal State 
in Switzerland 150 years ago. During a demonstration of the 
European Movement in Switzerland, the head of the Federal 
Department of Foreign Affairs said Tuesday evening [1 February] 
that there is "no realistic political alternative" to the 
European Union [EU] and that Switzerland should participate in 
it. 
  Increasingly, Europe is having to confront problems which 
extend beyond national borders. International crime, drug 
trafficking, and trade and environment policy cannot be resolved 
at regional or national level, the Federal Councillor said. 
  The EU is still far from perfect, he acknowledged, 
mentioning 
a bureaucracy which is still too dense and the failure of the 
negotiations on the Yugoslav conflict. Nevertheless, it is a 
stabilizing factor called upon to play a central role. 
  The future of the EU lies in a structure which respects 
minorities and which functions in a decentralized and federalist 
manner. It is here that Switzerland can make its contribution, 
Flavio Cotti stressed. A greater commitment by our country will 
not lead to the weakening of the Swiss identity. On the 
contrary, in greater Europe, Switzerland will continue to make 
decisions on its future itself. Moreover, it will become more 
sure of itself and more open to the world, he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

