<H3> <TI>   Diplomatic Relations With Macedonia Established </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0302090394 Bern ATSA/SDAA in French 1456 GMT 1 Feb 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0302090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern ATSA/SDAA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed BB: "Diplomatic Relations Between </F>
Switzerland and Macedonia"; as released by Bern ATSA/SDAA 
database] 
  [Text] Bern, 1 Feb (ATS) -- Mr. Franz Von Daeniken, head of 
the Political Section of the [Swiss] Federal Department of 
Foreign Affairs [DFAE], visited Skopje on Monday [31 January] 
and officially established diplomatic relations between 
Switzerland and the former Yugoslav republic of Macedonia, 
recognized by Switzerland on 12 May 1993. According to a 
communique released in Bern, Mr. von Daeniken's discussions 
dealt with the Balkan situation. 

</TEXT>

